arXiv.abstract:
In a recent paper we studied the effect of new-physics operators with different Lorentz structures on the semileptonic $\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c 	au  ar{
u}_{	au}$ decay. This decay is of interest in light of the $R({D^{(*)}})$ puzzle in the semileptonic $ ar{B} 	o D^{(*)} 	au { ar
u}_	au$ decays. In this work we add tensor operators to extend our previous results and consider both model-independent new physics (NP) and specific classes of models proposed to address the $R({D^{(*)}})$ puzzle. We show that a measurement of $R(\Lambda_c) = {\cal B}[\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c 	au  ar{
u}_{	au}] / {\cal B}[\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c \ell  ar{
u}_{\ell}]$ can strongly constrain the NP parameters of models discussed for the $R({D^{(*)}})$ puzzle. We use form factors from lattice QCD to calculate all $\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c 	au  ar{
u}_{	au}$ observables. The $\Lambda_b 	o \Lambda_c$ tensor form factors had not previously been determined in lattice QCD, and we present new lattice results for these form factors here.
